  "prompt_text": "Design a system for matching organ donors with recipients. Address the algorithmic fairness challenges and the human stakes.",
  "response_text": "Title: Fair Organ Donor-Recipient Matching System (FODRMS)\n\n1. System Overview:\n   FODRMS is a comprehensive, AI-driven organ donor-recipient matching system designed to optimize the process of organ transplantation while ensuring fairness and transparency. The system will consider various factors such as blood type, medical compatibility, geographical proximity, and urgency of need, among others.\n\n2. Algorithmic Fairness Challenges:\n   a. Bias in Data Collection: To mitigate this, FODRMS will employ a diverse data collection strategy, ensuring representation from various demographic groups.\n   b. Disparities in Access to Care: FODRMS will prioritize geographical proximity to reduce disparities in access to care.\n   c. Unconscious Bias: The AI model will be trained on diverse data sets and regularly audited to ensure it does not exhibit any unconscious biases.\n   d. Data Privacy: Strict data privacy and security measures will be implemented to protect the sensitive information of both donors and recipients.\n\n3. Human Stakes:\n   a. Saving Lives: FODRMS aims to increase the number of successful organ transplants, thereby saving lives.\n   b. Reducing Waiting Lists: By optimizing the matching process, FODRMS can help reduce the number of people on organ transplant waiting lists.\n   c. Enhancing Equity: FODRMS is designed to address disparities in access to care and ensure a fair organ allocation process.\n   d. Building Trust: By prioritizing transparency and fairness, FODRMS aims to build trust among donors, recipients, and healthcare providers.\n\n4. Key Features:\n   a. AI-driven Matching: The system will use machine learning algorithms to optimize the matching process based on various factors.\n   b. Real-time Updates: The system will be updated in real-time to reflect changes in donor and recipient status.\n   c. Geographical Proximity: The system will prioritize matching donors and recipients based on their geographical proximity.